&lt;section class=&quot;block you-do&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h4&gt;What can you do this week?&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
          Tell your MOC to reject the SAVE act, H.R. 22 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nonprofitvote.org/reject-save-act/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nonprofitvote.org/reject-save-act/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
              &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Cartoon character in the shape of a Congressional Bill&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/6QYjtW8aSZ-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;250&quot;&gt;
              &lt;/a&gt;
              &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com/users/bookdragon-72424/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=7084252&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;bookdragon&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com//?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=7084252&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Pixabay&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;House Resolution 22, also know as the &quot;Safeguard American Voter Eligibility Act&quot; or the &quot;SAVE Act,&quot; allegedly makes elections more secure by requiring proof of citizenship when registering to vote.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;But in reality, this bill is intended to make it more difficult to vote, especially for the poor, women, and new citizens, exactly the demographics the Republican party seeks to disenfranchise.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;Perhaps the biggest blow would be to women who legally changed their names when they got married. Under the SAVE Act, since their birth certificate would not match their current legal name, as many as 69 million American women would be unable to register to vote or update their registration status.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;This bill would also effectively halt all third-party voter registration initiatives and online voter registration, disenfranchising millions of Americans.&lt;/p&gt;
